Romans 12 verse six says, God has given each of us the ability to do certain things well.

22:33.554 --> 22:36.879
My oldest sister is an incredible singer.

22:38.001 --> 22:40.304
She literally can sing the stars down.

22:41.466 --> 22:44.370
When she was in high school, she discovered this,

22:44.482 --> 22:50.031
incredible gift God had given to her and she began to compete on a state level and she would win almost every time.

22:51.493 --> 22:58.223
And as an adult she began to be used by God in singing and church but in other venues too.

22:58.544 --> 23:02.770
And one day a talent scout

23:03.074 --> 23:05.556
talked to her and said, you got a great voice.

23:06.457 --> 23:10.000
I would love for you to do something else, and he was presented to her.

23:10.801 --> 23:13.784
But she said, now, I mean, it was secular songs.

23:14.064 --> 23:16.867
And she prayed about and thought about it, went back and told him no.

23:18.589 --> 23:21.451
She said, I have this gift, but I want a gift to God.

23:22.532 --> 23:24.274
And I'm not going to give to anybody else.

23:24.334 --> 23:26.156
So she made a decision not.

23:26.176 --> 23:28.418
And God has used her in an incredible way.

23:28.978 --> 23:30.860
My second, I've got two sisters.

23:31.060 --> 23:33.042
I'm the baby of the family.

23:33.250 --> 23:37.136
and the third, and my other sister's an excellent singer too.

23:37.436 --> 23:41.142
But when we got to me, I guess all the talent had been distributed.

23:41.322 --> 23:41.783
I don't know.

23:42.323 --> 23:43.004
It was all gone.

23:45.528 --> 23:55.683
So at my parents' 50th wedding anniversary, my two sisters came up with a great idea of, let's do a trio, and let's sing us on to our parents.

23:56.384 --> 23:58.548
The room was full of all extended family.

23:58.608 --> 24:00.210
It was just packed.

24:00.386 --> 24:02.849
And I said, no, you do a duet.

24:02.929 --> 24:04.011
No, we're going to do a trio.

24:04.051 --> 24:05.172
It's got to be all three of us.

24:05.973 --> 24:11.621
So finally I said yes, because I thought if I sang low, no one would be fine.

24:11.821 --> 24:13.703
And then I find out I have a solo.

24:13.723 --> 24:15.265
I have a section.

24:15.325 --> 24:17.668
All of us have a little section in that song.

24:17.709 --> 24:18.650
And I have a little solo.

24:19.331 --> 24:21.994
Every time I've ever done a solo, a solo no one can hear it.

24:22.675 --> 24:24.497
But they got to be able to hear it.

24:25.298 --> 24:26.280
I got to tell you something.

24:26.500 --> 24:27.221
I was so nervous.

24:27.261 --> 24:28.082
I didn't want to do.

24:28.898 --> 24:33.664
And we got into the song, there we are, places packed, my parents 50th anniversary.

24:33.684 --> 24:34.665
We're singing the song.

24:35.206 --> 24:39.912
And as we're singing the first part of the song, I realize, I can't remember any of the words I'm supposed to think.

24:40.492 --> 24:43.196
I did not remember any of the words.

24:43.716 --> 24:45.318
I went totally blank.

24:46.200 --> 24:47.862
So it came to my part.

24:48.362 --> 24:49.303
I knew the tune.

24:50.485 --> 24:52.347
I made up the words.

24:53.368 --> 24:55.872
Not one word came from the song.

24:56.352 --> 24:57.874
I made up all the words.

24:58.050 --> 25:00.073
And I rhymed it at the end.

25:01.775 --> 25:04.879
I don't know how it happened, but I got a rhyme at the end.

25:05.500 --> 25:09.926
And while I was singing it, my two sisters looked at me like, what is wrong with you?

25:10.267 --> 25:14.633
And I looked back at them and as I go with this, and it's all your fault.

25:15.134 --> 25:16.576
So just go with it.

25:17.998 --> 25:24.146
So I came to the end, I rhymed it at the end, we finished it, my parents never knew.

25:25.442 --> 25:27.865
No one in the rut, they plotted us.

25:27.945 --> 25:29.607
I had people coming, oh, you're amazing.

25:29.627 --> 25:30.388
I had no idea.

25:30.408 --> 25:38.497
And I realized, it doesn't matter what words you're saying, as long as it rhymes, people are fine.

25:38.537 --> 25:39.118
They go with it.

25:40.519 --> 25:46.747
I'm just saying, when God called me in the ministry, I knew it was not as a worship pastor.

25:46.767 --> 25:50.791
But I do have talents and you have talents.

25:51.793 --> 25:53.074
It's not the same ones.

25:55.714 --> 25:57.797
Tony Price has whole different talents than I have.

25:58.218 --> 26:02.745
We have different talents, you have different talents, but God wants you to use your talents.

26:03.106 --> 26:04.929
And you can't believe the amount of talents you have.

26:04.969 --> 26:07.012
Did you know a research was done on that too?

26:07.453 --> 26:10.337
How many talents does the average person have?

26:10.658 --> 26:12.120
And did you know what they came up with?

26:12.601 --> 26:13.062
500.

26:14.985 --> 26:21.515
Between five, the average person has between 500 and 700 talents.

26:22.717 --> 26:23.218
What?

26:25.890 --> 26:27.552
I've had so many people say, I have no talents.

26:27.572 --> 26:28.533
You got at least 500.

26:30.296 --> 26:32.278
You can do at least 500 things.

26:32.318 --> 26:34.101
Somebody else for least 700 things.

26:34.121 --> 26:35.422
You got more time.

26:35.442 --> 26:36.363
And here's what happens.

26:37.064 --> 26:40.849
Did you know that if you quit, you are never to retire from God?

26:42.852 --> 26:50.802
But there's some people at some point quit and you don't even know half your talents yet because God has intended you to go all the way.

26:52.546 --> 26:55.691
Learning new talents, learning new things that He built in you.

26:55.731 --> 26:57.073
This is His masterpiece.

26:57.093 --> 26:59.897
He's wanting you to understand that He put inside of you.

26:59.957 --> 27:03.783
And what I'm trying to say to you is that you are unfinished.

27:06.247 --> 27:07.288
You're not dead yet.

27:08.931 --> 27:13.778
God's done with you when you get to heaven, but if you're not in heaven, He ain't done with you.

27:13.838 --> 27:16.402
And He didn't want you to quit on Him.

27:17.442 --> 27:23.750
and there are things you can do and the impact that you can make for God and others, and he intends for you to do it.

27:23.770 --> 27:28.977
Keep learning, keep discovering this masterpiece he built you to be.

27:31.240 --> 27:36.647
So whatever it is you can do, do it for God.

27:38.289 --> 27:43.015
If you can repair a car, repair a car for the glory of God.

27:44.497 --> 27:45.618
It means you do your best.

27:47.810 --> 27:52.777
If you can balance financials, do it for the glory of God.

27:53.398 --> 27:58.224
If you can cook, do it for the glory of God.

27:59.205 --> 28:05.794
If you can run an office, do it for the glory of God.

28:05.955 --> 28:11.021
If you can catch a football, do it for the glory of God.

28:12.303 --> 28:17.330
I read a story this week about 20 of the players

28:17.442 --> 28:20.345
on the football team for Ohio State University.

28:20.745 --> 28:29.734
20 of the players who are all Christ followers got together and decided on this particular practice, we're all wearing Jesus T-shirts.

28:30.354 --> 28:32.717
And they said different things.

28:32.737 --> 28:40.544
Let's see, one said follow Jesus, one said Jesus won, Jesus saves, God's got me just here to give glory to God.

28:41.085 --> 28:46.610
All their T-shirts were different, but every one of them had a Jesus T-shirt on 20 ball players.

28:46.850 --> 28:49.834
And they decided on practice, this practice they were all wearing it.

28:50.115 --> 28:52.218
And you know what, I read that article and I said they got it.

28:52.739 --> 28:53.340
They understand.

28:53.380 --> 29:00.230
They know how, they have this talent in football and they're doing it for the glory of God.

29:00.490 --> 29:11.246
And every time I hear an athlete in any sport being interviewed and he talks about giving glory to God, I think to myself, oh my, so you understand.

29:12.508 --> 29:13.169
You understand.

29:13.509 --> 29:14.130
Listen.

29:14.242 --> 29:30.809
1 Corinthians 10 verse 31, whatever you do, do it all for the glory of God, whatever your talent, that means you do your best, it means you're totally honest, it means that you, and everything you do, do it for God.

29:31.170 --> 29:36.178
God, I'm giving you glory by doing this thing for this person.

29:37.058 --> 29:42.525
I went see one of my doctors, you know, there's all kinds of doctors, and I went to one of them.

29:42.846 --> 29:46.331
My doctors this week and a half ago, and I didn't have anything wrong with me.

29:46.351 --> 29:48.153
It was just a normal checkup.

29:48.914 --> 29:52.319
And when we were done, he said, well, let me pray for you.

29:54.602 --> 29:55.383
And he prayed for me.

29:57.105 --> 29:59.268
He didn't always do that, but he's done it before.

29:59.909 --> 30:02.873
And I thought to myself how meaningful that was to me.

30:02.973 --> 30:04.495
And I thought he gets it.

30:04.515 --> 30:06.418
He has the talent of doctoring.

30:07.458 --> 30:09.060
but he does it for the glory of God.

30:12.486 --> 30:16.091
Do whatever it is you do for his glory.

30:16.592 --> 30:20.037
So listen, you are talented and some of your 700s.

30:20.057 --> 30:23.763
And I'm very jealous.

30:26.006 --> 30:28.370
Our abilities show God's

30:28.674 --> 30:31.057
general direction in our life.

30:31.077 --> 30:31.878
This is important.

30:32.318 --> 30:39.566
Once we start discovering who we are, the greatest thing that happened to me is that I came to understand who I am.

30:39.586 --> 30:56.786
My talents, my abilities, my personality, my life experiences, I came to understand how I had been wired and what God wanted me to do with my life.

30:57.122 --> 30:58.584
It's the greatest thing in the world.

30:59.044 --> 31:02.708
If you don't come to understand who you are, you'll become nothing but a people pleaser.

31:03.589 --> 31:07.173
You just please in this person, in that person, in that person, just trying to make everybody happy.

31:07.453 --> 31:26.674
But when you come to discover who you are, how God made you, your talents and abilities, your strengths, all of this, you come to understand who you are, you get so released in life to be it without having to please everybody.

31:27.394 --> 31:32.582
Generally speaking, God uses our talents to help us discover who we are.

31:33.403 --> 31:39.672
Third of our abilities show what specific ministries that God has called us to do.

31:40.373 --> 31:46.723
Hebrews 13, 21 says, God will equip you with all you need for doing His will.

31:51.189 --> 31:54.514
Some of you, there's many in this church that are 700s.

31:56.514 --> 32:02.540
It's between 500, 700 talents, and there's a bunch of you that are 700s, and here's what I say to the 700 people.

32:03.601 --> 32:08.926
I'm saying to you, would you get out of your comfort zone since you can do anything?

32:10.768 --> 32:12.270
No matter what you do, it turns to gold.

32:12.590 --> 32:20.438
Get out of your comfort zone, do something that stretches you and moves our church's ministry to a new level.

32:21.239 --> 32:24.562
And I don't even know what that is, but I'm asking you, and I don't even,

32:24.802 --> 32:36.015
I just felt impressed to say this, and I don't know who it's to, but I'm challenging you to go out of your comfort zone to help take our church to another level.

32:36.696 --> 32:43.183
1 Corinthians chapter 9 verse 25 and 26 says this, all athletes are disciplined in their training.

32:43.483 --> 32:47.768
They do it to enterprise that will fade away, but we do it for an eternal prize.

32:48.189 --> 32:52.914
So I run with purpose in every step.

32:54.018 --> 32:55.821
I run with purpose in every step.

32:57.824 --> 32:59.447
Long ago, God gave me this verse.

33:00.308 --> 33:02.352
And he said, Mark, here's what I'm asking you to do.

33:02.392 --> 33:07.060
Every step from now to the end of your life, run with purpose.

33:07.100 --> 33:09.744
And I'm challenging every one of you.

33:09.764 --> 33:10.946
Don't just live.

33:11.447 --> 33:15.133
Don't just get up and go to bed the next night.

33:15.334 --> 33:16.035
Don't do that.

33:16.756 --> 33:20.402
Live with purpose, with purpose in every step.

33:20.674 --> 33:26.821
of your life and purpose will always be involved in blessing God and blessing others in some way.

33:28.082 --> 33:28.843
So how do you do this?

33:30.585 --> 33:34.069
Well, how do you get off the sidelines and into the game?

33:34.149 --> 33:34.770
How do you do that?

33:35.391 --> 33:48.626
Somebody said that church ministry is very much like a football game in which there are 22 people on the field in desperate need of rest and 60,000 people in the stadium

33:48.866 --> 33:51.189
with desperate need of exercise.

33:54.473 --> 33:55.495
And here's what I want to say.

33:55.555 --> 34:04.267
In church, it's so much that way, a handful of people are doing six and seven jobs because there's nobody else to pitch in and they get burned out.

34:05.268 --> 34:06.910
And I don't want ministry like that.

34:08.813 --> 34:16.162
Ministry was intended that every one of us do something to be a part, some ministry of some kind, some talent and ability that God has given us.

34:16.443 --> 34:18.866
Well, look, Mark, I've only got

34:19.170 --> 34:21.752
30 minutes, I can give a week.

34:21.773 --> 34:23.434
That's okay, we got 30 minute jobs here.

34:25.376 --> 34:28.259
No matter what you got, we got jobs for you.

34:29.240 --> 34:32.963
We got ministries that you can do with whatever time you have.

34:37.328 --> 34:42.933
But help somebody else, it's doing too many jobs in order to keep things going.

34:42.953 --> 34:48.178
Help someone else out so they don't have to do too many jobs.

34:48.898 --> 34:49.719
and say yes.

34:49.939 --> 34:51.021
Well, this is such a big church.

34:51.061 --> 34:51.741
They don't need me.

34:51.802 --> 34:53.544
No, the bigger the church, the more we need you.

34:54.665 --> 34:55.987
That's actually what is true.

34:56.367 --> 34:59.211
The bigger the church, the more we need you.

35:00.793 --> 35:01.594
So what do you do?

35:01.834 --> 35:05.759
First, take an honest look at the spiritual gifts, talents, and abilities God has given you.

35:06.820 --> 35:08.022
You don't have to be humble about it.

35:08.262 --> 35:11.286
You're really good at a whole bunch of things.

35:11.406 --> 35:14.930
And the more you learn, it's not,

35:15.138 --> 35:16.259
You don't have to be humble about it.

35:16.460 --> 35:16.900
Thank God.

35:16.920 --> 35:18.102
He's the one that did it, not you.

35:18.442 --> 35:19.764
He's given you talents.

35:21.526 --> 35:22.247
What do you do good?

35:24.911 --> 35:29.136
Keep an open heart about a new thing that God wants to do in your life.

35:29.957 --> 35:32.060
Second of all, dedicate all of yourself to God.

35:32.420 --> 35:34.163
All those talents, give them to God.

35:34.403 --> 35:41.352
He says in Romans 12, one, offer yourself as a living sacrifice to God, dedicated for His service and pleasing to Him.

35:41.372 --> 35:42.994
Take everything you can do.

35:43.106 --> 35:45.572
Whatever your talents and say, God, these are yours.

35:46.655 --> 35:48.560
Dedicate the living sacrifice.

35:49.022 --> 35:50.505
Three, develop your skills.

35:50.606 --> 35:51.688
Keep learning more.

35:51.769 --> 35:53.072
Keep growing more.

35:53.894 --> 35:54.877
Never arrive.

35:55.117 --> 35:55.960
Never arrive.

35:57.083 --> 35:58.386
Proverbs 19.

35:58.530 --> 36:01.052
Verse 8 says, do yourself a favor and learn all you can.

36:01.092 --> 36:03.074
Then remember what you've learned and you'll prosper.

36:03.395 --> 36:05.477
Keep growing, keep growing.

36:05.497 --> 36:12.123
In Ecclesiastes 10, 10, he says, if the ax is dull and its edge unsharpened, more strength is needed, but skill will bring success.

36:12.363 --> 36:16.807
There are times in which when we're doing something, the ax starts getting dull.

36:18.869 --> 36:19.630
Sharpen the ax.

36:19.650 --> 36:22.773
So you don't have to use as much energy.

36:23.073 --> 36:23.854
Sharpen the ax.

36:23.874 --> 36:25.756
Keep growing stronger.

36:25.856 --> 36:28.178
Keep getting more training.

36:28.642 --> 36:37.852
Here's the fourth thing, find a ministry in which you can use what God has given you to bless him and others.

36:38.132 --> 36:45.380
First Peter, chapter four verse 10 says, God has given to each of you some special abilities, be sure to use them to help each other.

36:45.420 --> 36:54.930
The reason for these talents is to use them to help each other.

36:55.714 --> 37:00.020
Now, I'm asking you, there is this QR code that's the first of the two.

37:00.060 --> 37:07.051
And I'm asking you this morning or this afternoon sometime, would you just scan it and see what's there?

37:07.471 --> 37:10.255
And I wonder if God is leading me to be a part of that.

37:10.275 --> 37:12.599
Well, you can respond, you'll get a response back.

37:14.862 --> 37:22.353
And maybe when you leave, go out into the Commons and explore worship or go in the next step center and explore any other ministry.

37:23.014 --> 37:25.618
And here's two questions I want to ask you, and we're done, and this is it.

37:27.746 --> 37:32.551
Why did God bring you to sugar creek?

37:34.814 --> 37:35.314
Here you are.

37:35.354 --> 37:38.198
Why did God bring you here?

37:39.139 --> 37:44.585
Yes, it was for this church to bless you and help you and help you to grow and know God better.

37:45.065 --> 37:45.646
That is true.

37:45.946 --> 37:51.292
But there was also a reason that he brought you here to give to other people.

37:52.754 --> 37:56.818
To use your abilities and talents to somebody else, not just everybody doing for you,

37:57.026 --> 37:58.629
you're doing now for others.

37:59.009 --> 38:04.658
And I'm asking you, open your heart to ministry.

38:04.678 --> 38:07.002
And here's the second.

38:07.022 --> 38:12.631
How could God use you to make a difference in this church?

38:14.253 --> 38:15.014
Because we need you.

38:17.078 --> 38:24.529
And I'm asking you to open your heart to some ministry that God is calling you to do.

38:24.549 --> 38:25.010
Let's pray.

38:25.474 --> 38:27.316
Lord, we thank You for the truth of Your Word.

38:27.377 --> 38:32.083
We thank You for how wonderful it is and You are trying to help grow us up.

38:33.445 --> 38:48.305
Part of spiritual maturity is spending time in Your Word and praying, but also part of spiritual maturity is giving back of our time, our talent, our energy in helping and blessing others.

38:48.365 --> 38:51.109
And as we do it, Lord, we're doing it for Your glory.

38:52.811 --> 38:55.154
So Father, I pray that You would touch

38:55.234 --> 39:00.000
the hearts of individuals who, for some reason, have just never gotten involved.

39:00.421 --> 39:02.724
For some reason, more involved than now aren't.

39:03.465 --> 39:12.817
And God, I pray that you would open up their heart for a new season of ministry to care for other people.

39:17.343 --> 39:20.788
And Father, as they serve, lighten the load for everybody else.

39:23.852 --> 39:25.234
And these things, I pray.

39:25.762 --> 39:27.954
In Jesus' name, amen.

